# Journal Drafts System — Full Implementation Plan

## Architecture Overview

The draft system mirrors the chapter draft pattern exactly: journals get a `status` column (`'draft' | 'published'`), the editor autosaves every 30 seconds as a server-side draft, and the user explicitly clicks "Publish" to make a post live. This is the cleanest approach because it keeps all draft state in the database (survives page refresh, browser close, device switch) and requires minimal structural change to the existing codebase.

---

## 1. Database Migration SQL

**New file: `server/sql/journal_drafts.sql`**

```sql
-- =============================================
-- Journal Drafts Feature
-- Safe to re-run (IF NOT EXISTS / OR REPLACE)
-- =============================================

-- Step 1: Add status column to journals
-- Default 'published' ensures zero-downtime — all existing rows become published instantly
ALTER TABLE public.journals
ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'published'
CHECK (status IN ('draft', 'published'));

-- Step 2: Add published_at column (nullable — NULL means never published)
ALTER TABLE public.journals
ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS published_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NULL;

-- Step 3: Backfill existing rows — set published_at = created_at for all current posts
UPDATE public.journals
SET published_at = created_at
WHERE published_at IS NULL AND status = 'published';

-- Step 4: Index for fast draft list queries (user's own drafts)
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_journals_drafts
ON public.journals(user_id, status, updated_at DESC)
WHERE status = 'draft';

-- Step 5: Index to ensure all public feeds remain fast
-- The existing idx_journals_following_feed covers (user_id, privacy, created_at DESC) WHERE privacy='public'
-- We need status='published' added to all feed queries — partial index helps
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_journals_published_feed
ON public.journals(privacy, created_at DESC, id DESC)
WHERE status = 'published' AND privacy = 'public';

-- Step 6: Update get_following_feed RPC to exclude drafts
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.get_following_feed(
    p_user_id UUID,
    p_limit INT DEFAULT 5,
    p_before TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NULL
)
RETURNS TABLE (
    id UUID, user_id UUID, title TEXT, preview_text TEXT,
    thumbnail_url TEXT, post_type TEXT, created_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
    privacy TEXT, views INT, is_repost BOOLEAN,
    repost_source_journal_id UUID, repost_caption TEXT,
    prompt_id INTEGER, user_name TEXT, user_image_url TEXT,
    user_badge TEXT, user_obj_id UUID,
    like_count BIGINT, reaction_count BIGINT,
    comment_count BIGINT, bookmark_count BIGINT
)
LANGUAGE sql STABLE SECURITY DEFINER SET search_path = public
AS $$
    SELECT j.id, j.user_id, j.title, j.preview_text, j.thumbnail_url,
           j.post_type, j.created_at, j.privacy, j.views, j.is_repost,
           j.repost_source_journal_id, j.repost_caption, j.prompt_id,
           u.name, u.image_url, u.badge, u.id,
           j.cached_reaction_count::bigint, j.cached_reaction_count::bigint,
           j.cached_comment_count::bigint, j.cached_bookmark_count::bigint
    FROM public.journals j
    INNER JOIN public.follows f ON f.following_id = j.user_id AND f.follower_id = p_user_id
    LEFT JOIN public.users u ON u.id = j.user_id
    WHERE j.privacy = 'public'
      AND j.status = 'published'           -- NEW: exclude drafts
      AND (p_before IS NULL OR j.created_at < p_before)
    ORDER BY j.created_at DESC, j.id DESC
    LIMIT p_limit;
$$;

